subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
(
Holotype
). Length: 8.25 mm. Color: reddish-orange; antennal club infuscate; the following black: mandibles, eyes, antennomeres 2–3 (in part) and 4–9 (entirely), legs (except proximal 4/5 of profemora and mesofemora, and proximal 3/4 of metafemora); pronotum with piceous longitudinal macula at middle, extending from anterior margin to beyond posterior limit of transverse impression; elytra with 4 black maculae (
Fig. 5
) that do not attain epipleura laterally. Abdomen: ventrite 5 with posterior angles rather broadly rounded, hind margin with a rather shallow, broad, V-shaped emargination; ventrite 6 narrower than ventrite 5, with hind angles more acute, and posterior emargination deeper at middle; tergite 6 concave ventrally, with hind margin narrowly rounded, surpassing posterior margin of ventrite 6.
